
=Bio=

"From November 2022 to October 2023, I was a Fellow at Harvard's Library Innovation Lab, which supported me in my work for a year. This fellowship was enabled by the Democratizing Open Knowledge program, which is funded by the Filecoin Foundation for the Decentralized Web, a "nonprofit organization committed to preserving humanity's most important information by fostering the development of open-source software and open protocols". As the name suggests, they are organized around the Filecoin project, which is a cryptocurrency/blockchain project. The fellowship had no strings attached as far as my independence in researching and analyzing the crypto industry, and I was not obligated to do any work relating to Filecoin (nor was I obligated not to). My focus at the LIL did not involve Filecoin specifically."

(https://www.mollywhite.net/crypto-disclosures/)

